324.1116.  Agency hiring criteria. — A private investigator agency or private fire investigator agency shall not hire any individual as an employee unless the individual:
  (1)  Is at least twenty-one years of age;
  (2)  Provides two recent photographs of themselves, of a type prescribed by the board of private investigator examiners;
  (3)  Has been fingerprinted in a manner approved by the Missouri state highway patrol, central repository, under section 43.543; and
  (4)  Complies with any other qualifications and requirements the board adopts by rule.
(L. 2007 H.B. 780 merged with S.B. 308, A.L. 2011 H.B. 464)
